modules.description: Provides functions to parse and generate OCaml syntax trees from quoted expressions, supporting custom syntax extensions. Works with abstract syntax tree nodes and literal representations of code. Enables creation of domain-specific notations within OCaml programs.

Checks if a given string is a quotation and processes embedded expressions and patterns within code. It manipulates AST nodes from the MLast module and integrates with ppx extensions. Used to transform syntax during compilation, enabling custom syntax extensions in OCaml code.
